author: Ural Garrett
title: How Similar Does Nicki Minaj's "No Frauds" Sound To Drake's "Summer Sixteen?"
text:
It’s been a week since Nicki Minaj released her Remy Ma diss track “No Frauds” and two other singles to make her #3PackFromParis trio. 
Though all three are getting Ms. Onika close to breaking her tie with Aretha Franklin for most Hot 100 charting singles, fans have noticed that the single featuring both Lil Wayne and Drake sound a little too similar to Drizzy’s “Summer Sixteen.” A post shared by Peppermint Petty🌴🐸 (@reikipedia) on Mar 14, 2017 at 9:58am PDT So Drake – Summer Sixteen and Nicki – No Frauds the same beat 🤔 😳😒 
— keanna|kiwii (@_NapoleonComplx) March 12, 2017 
The similarities make sense when one considers that both “No Frauds” and “Summer Sixteen” were both co-produced by Future and Travis Scott collaborator CuBeatz. 
Listen to both below and judge for yourself. 
“No Frauds” isn’t the only track that many have used to discredit Minaj’s creative credibility. 
#3PackFromParis single “Regret In Your Tears” led to many believing the song was aimed at the Queen Barbz’ former relationship with Meek Mill, but was supposedly written by PARTYNEXTDOOR. Minaj wholesomely denied the allegations before PARTY responded and then deleted his post on Twitter.
